United Kingdom":"Skircoat, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Copley, Metropolitan borough of Calderdale, West Yorkshire, England":"Copley, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1263–1321":"about 1263–1321","1263–1321":"1263–1321","1267–Female":"1267–Deceased","1299–1375":"1299–1375","1301–Female":"1301–Deceased","–1265":"–1265","1232–Female":"1232–Deceased","abt 1301":"about 1301","1316":"1316","1301":"1301","1267":"1267","1299":"1299","1321":"1321","1232":"1232","1265":"1265","1375":"1375","1263":"1263","about 1265":"about 1265","about 1263":"about 1263","Copley, Calderdale, England":"Copley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Copley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Copley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Skircoat, Halifax, West Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Skircoat, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Copley, Metropolitan borough of Calderdale, West Yorkshire, England":"Copley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Copley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): habitational name from any of various places called Copley, for example in County Durham, Staffordshire, and Yorkshire, from the Old English personal name <i>Coppa</i> (apparently a byname for a tall man) or from <i>copp</i> ‘hilltop’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Thomas de Copley was born about 1263, in Copley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Adam Copley ,Esq, and Ann Leventhorpe. He married Winnifred de Mirfield in 1299, in Skircoat, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1321, in his hometown, at the age of 59, and was buried in Skircoat, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1263–1321":"umbes 1263–1321","1263–1321":"1263–1321","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","1299–1375":"1299–1375","1301–Female":"1301–Surnud","–1265":"–1265","1232–Female":"1232–Surnud","abt 1301":"umbes 1301","1316":"1316","1301":"1301","1267":"1267","1299":"1299","1321":"1321","1232":"1232","1265":"1265","1375":"1375","1263":"1263","about 1265":"umbes 1265","about 1263":"umbes 1263","Copley, Calderdale, England":"Copley, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Copley, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Copley, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Skircoat, Halifax, West Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Skircoat, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Copley, Metropolitan borough of Calderdale, West Yorkshire, England":"Copley, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1263–1321"